Package grafioschtrader.service

Class GTNetExchangeSyncService

java.lang.Object
grafioschtrader.service.GTNetExchangeSyncService
@Service public class GTNetExchangeSyncService extends Object
Service for synchronizing GTNetExchange configurations between GTNet peers. Handles the bidirectional exchange of which instruments each server is willing to share price data for, and updates GTNetSupplierDetail accordingly.

Flow for AC_OPEN Bidirectional Exchange

  1. Local server sends GT_NET_EXCHANGE_SYNC_SEL_RR_C with changed GTNetExchange items since last sync
  2. Remote server updates its GTNetSupplierDetail based on received items
  3. Remote server responds GT_NET_EXCHANGE_SYNC_RESPONSE_S with its own changed items
  4. Local server updates its GTNetSupplierDetail based on response

    • recreateSupplierDetails

      @Transactional public void recreateSupplierDetails(GTNet supplier, List<ExchangeSyncMsg.ExchangeSyncItem> items)
      Recreates ALL GTNetSupplierDetail entries for a peer. Deletes all existing entries first, then creates new ones from response items. Used for full recreation mode to ensure complete synchronization.
      Parameters:
      supplier - the remote GTNet server that sent the items
      items - the list of exchange sync items from the remote server

    • updateSupplierDetails

      @Transactional public void updateSupplierDetails(GTNet supplier, List<ExchangeSyncMsg.ExchangeSyncItem> items)
      Updates GTNetSupplierDetail entries based on received sync items from a remote peer. For each item:
      • If lastpriceSend is true, create/update supplier detail for INTRADAY
      • If lastpriceSend is false, delete supplier detail for INTRADAY (if exists)
      • If historicalSend is true, create/update supplier detail for HISTORICAL
      • If historicalSend is false, delete supplier detail for HISTORICAL (if exists)
      Parameters:
      supplier - the remote GTNet server that sent the items
      items - the list of exchange sync items from the remote server
